## Submit payload (`purchaseRequest`)

**Encoding:** Always send as `data=<JSON>` field (NOT flat URL-encoded params):
```js
const sendParams = new URLSearchParams();
sendParams.append('data', JSON.stringify(payload));
```
This matches the voucher.html pattern and reliably flows through the Vercel proxy → GAS `params.data → JSON.parse(params.data)`.

Fields in the JSON payload:
```text
action, prNo, companyCode, companyName, department, requesterName, requesterEmail,
requiredDate, priority, currency, items (JSON string of line objects),
grandTotal, purpose,
vendorName, vendorType, vendorTaxId, vendorAddress,
vendorAccountName, vendorAccountNo, vendorBankName, vendorTransferNote,
budgetCode, budgetApprover, supplierApprover, submittedAt,
requesterSignature (base64), attachments (JSON string of [{fileName, fileData, mimeType}])
```

## Items line object structure

Each row in `items` JSON array uses:
```js
{ section, loai, desc, qty, unit, price, total, note }
```
**Key field is `desc`** (from `.item-desc` input) — NOT `name` or `itemName`.

When rendering items in the drawer or print view, always check `item.desc` first:
```js
item.desc || item.name || item.itemName || '—'
```

## Attachments (supporting documents)

- Collected as `File` objects in `_attachmentFiles[]`
- At submit time, converted to base64 via `_fileToBase64()` and sent as `attachments` JSON string inside the `data` field
- GAS backend (`handlePurchaseRequest`) uploads to Drive via `DriveApp` using folder ID from `getCfg_('PURCHASE_REQUEST_FOLDER_ID', '1SJ-pUa6jg2rmJTzle-TvvSNrKMUduvx3')`
- Drive URLs stored in `metadata.attachments[]` as `{fileName, fileUrl}`
- **Never use `/api/drive-upload`** (no Service Account quota on personal Drive)

## Email notifications after submit

`handlePurchaseRequest` calls `sendPurchaseRequestEmails_(data, prNo)` after saving:
- Requester (`data.requesterEmail`) gets confirmation email
- Budget approver (`data.budgetApprover`) and supplier approver (`data.supplierApprover`) get approval-request emails

**Submit UX:** Spinner; **network `catch`** shows error toast (`submitForm`).

---

## Caching (`getMasterData`)

- Keys: **`tlc_master_data`**, **`tlc_master_data_timestamp`**; TTL **30 minutes** stale-while-revalidate.
- Cache renders immediately then background refresh.
- **Shared** with `voucher.html` and all other workflows — one cache, one source of truth. If an employee is added/updated in the Master sheet, clearing `tlc_master_data` from localStorage on any page refreshes it for all.

